how to identify and treat
hypothermia & frostbite
hypothermia
How do you treat hypothermia?
Mild Hypothermia
95 F and 89.6 F (35 C and 32 C)
Moderate Hypothermia
89.6 F and 82.4 F (32 C and 28 C)
Severe Hypothermia
< 82.4 F (28 C)
continued >
frostbite
If you have signs or symptoms of surface or deep frostbite, which are the second
and third stages of frostbite, visit a healthcare provider immediately for
treatment. Time is critical with frostbite. You may experience severe pain with
frostbite as your skin thaws.
